    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-08-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-08-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="186"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                <head>186. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_NRM1" type="from"
                        >Nixon</persName> to his Assistant for National Security Affairs (<persName
                        corresp="#p_KHA1" type="to">Kissinger</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d186fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1"
                            >Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files, Box 1023, Presidential/<gloss target="#t_HAK1"
                            >HAK</gloss>
                        <gloss target="#t_Memcon1">MemCon</gloss>s, The President and President
                            <persName corresp="#p_CN1">Ceausescu</persName>. No classification
                        marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-08-07">August 7, 1969</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On our trip we made a number of commitments as you may recall which involve
                    following up. For example with <persName corresp="#p_CN1">Ceausescu</persName>,
                    he <pb facs="0503" n="459" xml:id="pg_459"/> wanted a group to come in and give
                    him some advice on irrigation, also, I told him that we would have <persName
                        corresp="#p_DBDLA1">DuBridge</persName> come over with a scientific group.
                        <persName corresp="#p_DBDLA1">DuBridge</persName>, incidentally, is going to
                    Yugoslavia in September and it might be that that would be the time that he
                    could make this move. I think <persName corresp="#p_HDCM1">Hardin</persName> and
                    possibly <persName corresp="#p_HJA1">Hannah</persName> might go to Rumania on
                    the irrigation project. We donʼt want to place too heavy a hand here, but this
                    kind of visit will not get much publicity and would be enormously helpful in
                    letting <persName corresp="#p_CN1">Ceausescu</persName> have some little goodies
                    that he can tell his associates about as to how dealing with the <gloss
                        target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> really pays. This of course is only one
                        example.<note n="2" xml:id="d186fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> relayed the Presidentʼs
                        desires to <persName corresp="#p_HDCM1">Hardin</persName> in memoranda of
                        August 11 and 29. <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> also sent
                        a memorandum outlining the Presidentʼs interest in promoting trade with
                        Romania to <persName corresp="#p_SMH1">Stans</persName> on August 11. Copies
                        of the memoranda are ibid., Box 702, Country Files—Europe, Romania, Vol.
                        I—8/69.</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Omitted here is information unrelated to Romania.]</p>
            </div>
